<div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:mt-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
  <div class="md:flex md:justify-between">
    <div></div>

    <div class="sm:flex sm:justify-center md:justify-start">
      <div class="mt-3 sm:mt-0 sm:ml-3">
        <div data-controller="resume" data-resume-url-value="<%= home_download_resume_path %>">
          <div id="download-pdf-button" data-action="click->resume#download" class="cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-3 border border-transparent text-base font-medium rounded-md text-indigo-600 bg-indigo-100 hover:bg-indigo-200 md:py-4 md:text-lg md:px-10">
            Download PDF
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="md:hidden my-4 text-gray-500">
    I know, I know...here I am saying that this website is 100% responsive meanwhile I have some funky word breaks in this view on mobile.
    <br/><br/>
    I wanted to dynamically generate PDFs based on the contents of this view (rather than serve a static file) so I have chosen to allow some less-than-ideal formatting on mobile in order to preserve the styling of the PDF. 
  </div>

  <%= render partial: 'resume_body' %>
</div>
